# Figma Implementation Rules

1. **Prioritize Data over Visuals**: Never rely only on screenshots. Always fetch the node JSON and extract exact layout/style values (spacing, gap, colors, font size).
2. **Deep Inspection**: When a node is selected, recursively inspect children to understand layout logic. Pay attention to `layoutMode`, `primaryAxisAlignItems`, and `counterAxisAlignItems`.
3. **Variable & Style Resolution**: Resolve Figma `styles` and `variables` IDs to project tokens (Tailwind config, CSS variables, theme objects). Avoid hardcoded hex values when a named variable exists.
4. **Code Connect First**: If Code Connect is available, treat `component documentation` and linked snippets as the source of truth for implementation.
5. **Auto-layout to CSS**: Translate Auto-layout semantics to CSS Flexbox/Grid, including `space-between`, hugging content, and fill behaviors.
6. **Prefer Existing UI Primitives**: Map Figma elements to existing design-system components in the codebase before introducing new custom components.
7. **Token-safe Diffs**: During review, reject style regressions that replace semantic tokens with raw constants unless there is an explicit exception.
8. **SVG-first Figma assets**: When bringing **resources** from Figma into this repo (icons, logos, non-photo graphics), **use SVG whenever possible**. Prefer exporting or reconstructing **vector** artwork as `.svg` (inline React components or imported static assets—follow existing patterns in `src/`). Do **not** default to Figma MCP **raster** URLs (`figma.com/api/mcp/asset/…` PNGs) or stacks of raster slices for crisp UI icons; reserve raster for genuinely bitmap-only art (photos, textured bitmaps) and document the exception. For compound vector icons, prefer a **single merged SVG** over many tiny PNG layers.
9. **Prefer `download_figma_images` for file-backed SVGs**: When the Cursor MCP server **`project-0-task-console-figma`** is available, use tool **`download_figma_images`** (`fileKey`, `localPath`, `nodes[]` with `nodeId` + `fileName` ending in `.svg`) to write exports next to the consuming code (for example under `src/components/icon/icons/`). Requires a valid **`FIGMA_API_KEY`** for that server (and file access). After download, prefer **inline React SVG components** (see `src/components/icon/icons/`) or keep a co-located `.svg` when the asset must stay static (e.g. pattern + embedded bitmap).